[
    {
        "content": "<p>A common theme throughout the combinatorial game library in Lean is that although we can define products on pre-games, we can't do so on games, since the operation can't be lifted. But do we have an actual counterexample?</p>",
        "id": 461970611,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1723502389
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think this would make for a nice file in the <code>Counterexamples</code> folder</p>",
        "id": 461970637,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1723502401
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't know of any myself</p>",
        "id": 461970684,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1723502410
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Just found this: <a href=\"https://math.stackexchange.com/a/2922745/718671\">https://math.stackexchange.com/a/2922745/718671</a></p>",
        "id": 461971311,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1723502809
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Watch out, I spent over a year trying to formalize a counterexample from Math.SE! Maybe this one is easier :)</p>",
        "id": 461971386,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1723502865
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The game </p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>K</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>∗</mo><mo>+</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>0</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mn>0</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">K = \\ast + \\{-1, 0|0, 1\\}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∗</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord\">−</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0∣0</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>apparently satisfies K ≈ 0 but K² ≉ 0</p>",
        "id": 461971472,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1723502898
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This counterexample was built to satisfy the additional constraint of being equivalent to a number, though</p>",
        "id": 461971707,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1723503057
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So there might exist something simpler</p>",
        "id": 461971711,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1723503061
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That being said this is a pretty simple game already</p>",
        "id": 461972251,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1723503460
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>...I think I found a mistake</p>",
        "id": 462016448,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1723523972
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Let <code>G = {0 | 0}</code>, <code>H = {-1, 0 | 0, 1}</code>.  For <code>GH ≈ 0</code>, each left move of it must be <code>⧏</code> than 0, but the moves <code>0 * H + G * 0 + 0 * 0</code> are not.</p>",
        "id": 462017515,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1723524287
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I did prove <code>K ≈ 0</code>, so there's a chance the result still works</p>",
        "id": 462019290,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1723525081
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh wait I think this can be salvaged</p>",
        "id": 462021161,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1723525649
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>G ≈ H but GG ≉ GH</p>",
        "id": 462021179,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1723525677
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/15764\">#15764</a></p>",
        "id": 462024124,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1723527203
    }
]